    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing, a single failure isn't what it is. it's everything. the version of me that people loved, the version that actually had a future... that person is dead. i can feel it. the whole identity i built is just gone. there's no \"rebuilding\" someone who doesn't exist anymore.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a heavy weight to carry the feeling that your entire identity has vanished, but that feeling is a symptom of your current pain, not an objective truth. The person you were is a collection of experiences, and those experiences don't vanish with one mistake; they simply evolve. Instead of trying to rebuild a past version, perhaps you can begin to acknowledge and accept the person you are *right now*, even in this broken state. That new starting point is where true change begins.",
      "source": "target",
